<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Welcomes Agreement on KLA Disarmament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Greece on Wednesday welcomed the
agreement reached between NATO and the Kosovo Liberation Army
(KLA) on the latter's disarmament.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after a two-day U.S.-Greek High Level Consultative
Committee (HLCC) meeting on the northeastern Aegean island of
Limnos, Greece's Deputy Defense Minister Dimitris Apostolakis said
that Greece was satisfied with the agreement between NATO and KLA
on its disarmament, a commitment that must be observed with the
same consistency which the Yugoslav side showed by withdrawing its
forces from Kosovo, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
As for the Cyprus problem, he said that the imperative priority
in the Cyprus issue was for all U.N. resolutions to be utilized in
a specific agreement, in line with the recent call by the seven
Western countries and Russia, known as the Group of Eight.
</P>
<P>
Apostolakis called on Turkey not to encourage the intransigency
of the Turkish Cypriot side and turn a new page.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Assistant Secretary of Defense Franklin Kramer attended
the annually HLCC meeting that addresses U.S.-Greek defense
cooperation and regional security issues, including the Cyprus
problem.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
