<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angolan Army Launches Attack on Rebels in Central </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan Army has launched
attack on the rebel UNITA troops in a town near Malanje City,
capital of the central Malanje Province, a military source said
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The unidentified source disclosed that the government army
occupied the town of Cambondo, killing some 100 troops of the
National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
The source added that two UNITA soldiers, three TMT-2 tanks and
50 light weapons were captured.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Angolan Army took the action in response to
the increased operation of the UNITA forces in the areas
neighboring Malanje recently.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the UNITA forces resumed bombardment on
the provincial city last Sunday. They used long-range artillery,
killing nine civilians, wounding 10 others and destroying six
houses.
</P>
<P>
The scared residents were forced to flee the city.
</P>
<P>
Since the civil war renewed in the southern African country
last December, the city of Malanje has been the main target of the
UNITA fire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
