<HEADLINE> 17 Illegal Cars Delivered to Israeli Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian police Wednesday
handed over 17 illegal cars to their Israeli counterparts in
Ramallah and Beira provinces, Voice of Palestine Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
A Palestinian police liaison official was quoted by the radio
that the disposed vehicles include cars believed to have been
stolen from the Israelis.
</P>
<P>
The police will also hand over some unlicensed cars found in
other Palestinian provinces to the Israelis later this week,
said the official.
</P>
<P>
Car stealing has been rampant for years in the Palestinian
self-ruled areas and the Palestinian citizens have been under
threat of death at the hands of those who drive unlicensed
vehicles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
