<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, June 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran on Wednesday lashed out at the United States for
its allegation on Tehran's weapon programs and termed the
U.S. move "ineffective and useless."
</P>
<P>
Tehran's anger came after U.S. Assistant Secretary of State
for Near East Affairs Martin Indyk, who was currently in Abu
Dhabi, the United Arab Emirates, accused Iran of developing
weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Hamid Reza Asefi said that
the U.S. "destructive" approach aimed at diverting public opinion
from the threats of Israel and selling more arms to regional
states, are "inefficient and useless." (BC-Iran-US-Weapons)
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Two Lebanese civilians were wounded Wednesday in an
Israeli bombardment on villages in south Lebanon, the Voice of the
People radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Abdelhadi Fahs, 70, and Ali Zahweh, 12, were injured when
their house in the village of Kabrikha on the north of the
Israeli occupied border zone in south Lebanon, was hit by an
Israeli shell.
</P>
<P>
The attack came as a response to previous operations launched
by guerrillas of the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God,
on Israel's positions inside the occupied zone.
(BC-Lebanon-Civilians-Wounded)
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- A Tehran local court on Wednesday sentenced
Gholamreza Qobeh, former Deputy Mayor of the Iranian Capital to
nine years in prison and barred him from holding government post
for good.
</P>
<P>
Qobeh was convicted of offenses ranging from embezzlement to
illegal occupation of municipality's properties, collaboration in
embezzlement and lobbying in government dealings, the Islamic
Republic News Agency reported. (BC-Iran-Mayor-Convicted)
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Arab League Secretary General Esmat Abdel-Meguid on
Wednesday accused Israel of violating the Fourth Geneva Convention
and international law.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid said Israel conducts illegal practices against the
Palestinians in the occupied Palestinian land, including torture,
demolition of Palestinian houses and confiscation of land.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League chief slammed Israel in a speech at the second
international symposium on international law and armament control
organized by the league in tandem with the Egyptian Society of
Criminal Law, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
(BC-Arab League-Israel) 
</P>
</TEXT>
