<HEADLINE> U.S. Soldiers in Kosovo Kill Two Assailants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 23 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Marines manning a
checkpoint in Kosovo came under fire Wednesday by unidentified
assailants and then returned fire, killing two people, the
commander of U.S. forces in Kosovo said.
</P>
<P>
In an interview from his Kosovo headquarters with reporters at
the Pentagon, Army Brig. Gen. John Craddock said the confrontation
began about noon EDT (East Daylight-saving Time) and was
continuing.
</P>
<P>
The general said it was still unclear whether the two killed
were military or civilian or whether they were Serbs or ethnic
Albanians.
</P>
<P>
He added that a similar incident occurred on Monday night when
members of the U.S. Army's 82nd Airborne Division were fired on,
but that nobody was killed and that three men were later taken
into custody by the soldiers. 
</P>
