<HEADLINE> 28 Countries to Attend Int'l Trade Fair in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 23 (Xinhua) -- More than 300 exhibitors
from 28 countries have confirmed to attend the 23rd Dar es Salaam
International Trade Fair next month, Director General of the
Tanzanian Board of External Trade Mbarouk Mwandoro said here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The exhibitors will display their goods either as private
individuals or as representatives of their countries during July
2-10 at the fair, Mwandoro told reporters.
</P>
<P>
The participating countries include Russia, the United States,
Zambia, Britain, China, South Africa, Uganda, Kenya, France, and
Japan, he said.
</P>
<P>
The fair is organized by the Tanzanian Board of External Trade
and supported by the Ministry of Industries and Commerce, Tanzania
Chamber of Commerce, Industry and Agriculture, together with the
Confederation of Tanzania Industries.
</P>
<P>
Senior information officer of the external trade board,
Emmanuel Buliki, said earlier that 30,000 square meters of
interior rentable space of the international trade fair is fully
booked.
</P>
<P>
The Dar es Salaam International Trade Fair has established
itself over years as the window for Tanzanian products as well as
goods of east, central and southern Africa.
</P>
<P>
The fair acts as one stop center for reaching countries such as
Uganda, Rwanda, Burundi, the Democratic Republic of Congo, Zambia,
Malawi, Zimbabwe and Botswana.
</P>
<P>
Participation in the fair has been on the increase from a mere
over 100 companies in late 1980s to over 1,000 firms last year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,021 exhibitors attended the 1998 fair, 234 of
which were based overseas. Twelve foreign nations participated at
an official level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
