<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Says Enough Fertilizer for Coming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's National Fertilizer
Agency announced Wednesday that over 400,000 tons of fertilizer in
its warehouse are more than sufficient for the coming crop season
starting from June this year.
</P>
<P>
Tibebu Haile, marketing department head of the agency, told the
press that the Ethiopian government allocates 100 million U.S.
dollars for purchasing fertilizer annually.
</P>
<P>
Tibebu said current fertilizer stock would reach well over
490,000 tons when an already ordered fertilizer reaches the
country soon.
</P>
<P>
At present, fertilizer is being distributed to farmers through
seven fertilizer importing companies in the Horn of Africa
country, he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that each state of the country should take measures to
 facilitate conditions for a speedy distribution of fertilizer
among farmers so that they can produce crop in the big rainy
season.
</P>
<P>
The crop in the big rainy season from June to September
accounts for almost 90 percent of the total output of the whole
year, according to the official. 
</P>
