airline, a move the Greek government says is vital for the
airline's survival.
</P>
<P>
The Greek government has sunk billions of drachmas into
ill-fated restructuring programs and repeatedly covered debts at
Olympic Airways.
</P>
<P>
The Greek national carrier is now facing more domestic
competition since small private airlines serving Greek islands and
other domestic airports are just getting off the ground this
Summer and are expected to bite into Olympic Airways' share.
