<HEADLINE> Iran to Expand Cooperation With U.N. Organization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Iranian ministries and state
organs are to expand cooperation with the United Nations
Industrial Development Organization (UNIDO), the Islamic Republic
News Agency reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Massoud Homayounfar, Director of UNIDO Coordination Office at
the Iranian Industries Ministry, said that seven UNIDO experts
came to Iran on Sunday to visit various organizations and
ministries and discuss issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
"During its 10-day stay in Tehran, the UNIDO delegation will
prepare a draft proposal on a comprehensive plan and will submit
it to the UNIDO board of directors for approval," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official noted that the cooperation is in line
with the reorganization of the UNIDO and the necessity of
coordination with UNIDO for better implementation of the country's
economic development plans.
</P>
<P>
Areas of cooperation includes small-medium scale industries,
efficient use of energy, preservation of environment, expansion
of agricultural and food industries, investment promotion schemes
and application of new technology in electronics and
biotechnology, he said.
</P>
<P>
Homayounfar said there is coordination between various
governmental organizations and UNIDO experts on important issues
related to the country's development plan.
</P>
<P>
He said that UNIDO generally formulates plans concerning
economic competitiveness, reduction of pollution and environmental
degradation, and expansion of productive employment in the
developing countries.
</P>
<P>
UNIOD's reorganization plan does not envision specific funds
to be provided to developing countries, but only acts as a
consultant to these countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
The funds need for the approved projects between UNIDO and
governmental organizations and ministries have to be raised from
international financial institutions such as the World Bank and
United Nations Development Program, he added. 
</P>
