<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Tehran Deputy Mayor Sent to Prison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 23 (Xinhua) -- A Tehran local court on Wednesday
sentenced Gholamreza Qobeh, former Deputy Mayor of the Iranian
Capital to nine years in prison and barred him from holding
government post for good.
</P>
<P>
Qobeh was convicted of offenses ranging from embezzlement to
illegal occupation of municipality's properties, collaboration in
embezzlement and lobbying in government dealings, the Islamic
Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The former deputy mayor in charge of executive and financial
affairs was also sentenced to 50 lashes and a fine of 27.963
billion rials (about 9.3 million U.S. dollars) along with two
times worth of 225 free-price gold coins.
</P>
<P>
He was also ordered to return to public treasury about 160.175
billion rials (about 53.39 million dollars), 225 free-price gold
coins, plus about 13.981 billion rials (4.66 million dollars) of
embezzled money.
</P>
<P>
Qobeh was a major assistant to former Tehran Mayor
Gholamhussein Karbaschi, who had been jailed in April for two
years prison terms on graft charges.
</P>
<P>
Karbaschi, close ally of former Iranian President Hashemi
Rafsanjani and strong supporter of President Mohammad Khatami,
has denied all the charges against him and termed the cases
against Tehran municipal officials as a politically-motivated
action by the conservatives against the moderates.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that some other officials of Karbaschi's
municipality would be put on trial in the future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
