<HEADLINE> Prince Ranariddh Returns From China Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian National Assembly
President Prince Norodom Ranariddh returned home Thursday from a
week-long official visit to China at the invitation of his Chinese
counterpart Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh and his party were greeted at the Pochentong Airport
by National Assembly Vice President Heng Samrin and government
leaders as well as some diplomats including Chinese Ambassador to
Cambodia Yan Tingai.
</P>
<P>
The prince told reporters at the airport that his trip was
"very successful." He said he believed the visit will further
strengthen the traditional friendly relations between the two
countries, especially the cooperation between the two parliaments.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the Prince highly appraised the tremendous
achievements made by Chinese people in recent years which he said
have impressed him deeply.
</P>
<P>
It was Ranariddh's first visit to China since he assumed
presidency of the National Assembly last November.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in China, the prince met with some senior
Chinese leaders including Li Peng, chairman of China's National
People's Congress Standing Committee and Li Ruihuan, chairman of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
Besides exchanging views on issues of common concern, the two
sides also expressed their hope to continue to support and help
each other and increase their mutually-beneficial cooperation
while building their own futures.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Beijing, Ranariddh also toured China's southern
city of Guangzhou and southwest Yunnan Province and visited
several enterprises. He briefed on the political situation and
investment environment in Cambodia and encouraged Chinese
enterprises to invest in Cambodia in such areas as agriculture and
tourism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
