<HEADLINE> Thailand to Organize Trade Fair to Boost Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Board of Investment
(BOI), a government agency affiliated to the Prime Minister's
Office, will organize a grand trade exhibition early next year to
demonstrate the potential of the Thai economy, BOI
Secretary-General Staporn Kavitanon said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Quoted by the Thai News Agency (TNA), Staporn said the grand
trade exhibition, dubbed "BOI Fair 2000", would be held between
February 1 and 17, 2000.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair is aimed at helping spur economic activities and
show momentous potential how the economy could get a good
re-starting after two years' plugging in its worst crisis, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Unlike the previous fair, held by the agency in 1995, companies
taking part in the fair would be allowed to sell their products to
visitors in a bid to help spark promising prospects for local
businesses.
</P>
<P>
The trade exhibition, with a large number of participating
companies and manufacturers as well as over 3 million expected
visitors, would also help boost confidence in the Thai economy
among international investors and consumers, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
