<HEADLINE> Greenpeace Members Stage Protest in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Members of the environmental
organization "Greenpeace" on Thursday staged a demonstration
outside Greece's Development Ministry in Athens to draw attention
to the problem of dioxin contamination and genetically modified
animal feed.
</P>
<P>
Dressing as chickens, the protestors placed barrels with the
indication "toxic dioxins" and sacks of "modified animal feed" in
front of the entrance to the ministry and asked Minister Evangelos
Venizelos to take all the necessary measures to safeguard public
health, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
In Greece, dioxin pollution was some 135 grams annually, mainly
from industrial installations, and this was roughly 67,500 times
greater than the amount which caused the recent food scandal in
Belgium, the "Greenpeace" said. 
</P>
