<HEADLINE> Developing Sino-Russian Friendship Throughout Generations (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- In the mind of Oleg Korolyov, vice-
chairman of Russia's Federation Council, his China mission is not
only to promote economic and trade cooperation between localities
in the two countries, but is to say hello to the Chinese people
for his father.
</P>
<P>
"Before I came here, my father told me that I should express
respect for the great, diligent and brotherly Chinese people for
him during my visit. Now I can go home after fulfilling this
mission, " said Korolyov today at the end of a six-day visit to
China.
</P>
<P>
Korolyov's 86-year-old father, who once served as a former U.S.
S.R. Red Army member, joined the Chinese people in fighting
against Japan's invasion of China in northeast China more than a
half century ago.
</P>
<P>
"That experience left him with good memories, and I learned
about China and the Chinese people from his experience," Korolyov
said, adding that "I feel proud that my father joined the War of
Resistance against Japan."
</P>
<P>
Talking about the special sentiments of his family toward China,
Korolyov said that the tradition of Sino-Russian friendship was
not only inherited in his family, but also was rooted in the
hearts of the Russian people.
</P>
<P>
"The fine tradition of mutual support and cooperation,
initiated by the previous generations, should be carried on," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Korolyov was here for a Sino-Russian seminar on regional
cooperation oriented toward the 21st century, at which he said
that the potential in economic and trade cooperation between
localities in the two countries needs to be tapped to help promote
the further growth of Sino-Russian friendly relations in the next
century.
</P>
<P>
Russia is fully prepared to cooperate with China in energy,
metallurgy, agriculture and high technology, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
