<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Stock Market Reaches New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- China's two stock exchanges
reported a record transaction volume at 62.3 billion yuan (about 7.
5 billion U.S. dollars) today.
</P>
<P>
The previous record of 51.4 billion yuan was set on June 15.
</P>
<P>
The trading volume at the Shanghai Stock Exchange hit 33.1
billion yuan, nearly 3.7 billion yuan more than the previous
record set on June 17, while the Shenzhen Stock Exchange reported
a trading volume of 29.2 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai composite index closed at 1654.11 points, higher
than yesterday's record high of 1606.50 points. While Shenzhen's
stock index reached 4404.6 points, up 5.46 percent from yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Stocks of large state-owned enterprises remained the hottest
buys on the Shanghai Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts here said a commentary published a few weeks
ago in the People's Daily, China's leading newspaper, urging
people to invest in the stock market and a speech made by the
chairman of the China Securities Regulatory Committee boosted
people's confidence in the stock market and the economy, and the
bullish market is a reflection of this confidence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
