<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 14:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Katyusha Rockets Fired into Northern Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Hours after a Lebanese woman was
wounded by Israeli shelling, a total of 15 Katyusha rockets were
slammed into northern Israel Thursday afternoon, Lebanese security
sources said.
</P>
<P>
It is still unknown whether the rockets that were launched from
south Lebanon had caused casualties or damage, the sources said,
adding no group has so far claimed responsibility for the attack.
</P>
<P>
Guerrillas of the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God,
always fired Katyushas into Israel when Israeli operations caused
casualty on Lebanese civilians.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, a Lebanese woman was wounded during an
Israeli shelling on her village of Kabrikha just north of the
Israeli occupied border zone in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
She is the sixth civilian injured by Israeli shelling in the
same village in five days.
</P>
<P>
Two civilians were wounded in the village on Wednesday and
three on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli attacks came as a response to previous operations
launched by Lebanese guerrillas spearheaded by Hezbollah to oust
Israeli troops and its ally South Lebanon Army out of the
country.
</P>
<P>
But, a 1996 agreement reached between Israel and Hezbollah
after an Israeli 16-day blitz on Lebanon banned any attacks
from civilian area or on civilians.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon
in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from
Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
