<HEADLINE> Jiang Issues Decree On Promulgating Military Establishment Regulations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Central Military
Commission Jiang Zemin has recently issued a decree on
promulgating regulations on military establishment of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army (PLA), the first regulations of the kind
in the history of the PLA.
</P>
<P>
Chinese military establishment is handled by the Central
Military Commission and its authorized units, including the
establishment of military organizations, weapons and other
facilities, and the authorized size of the army.
</P>
<P>
The regulations cover the whole process of military
establishment, offering a thorough legal reference in this respect
which must be respected by every member of the PLA.
</P>
<P>
The Headquarters of General Staff of the PLA requires all
military personnel to study the regulations and promote the
modernization of the army. 
</P>
</TEXT>
