<HEADLINE> Vice-President Stresses Ideological, Political Awareness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
has emphasized the importance of increased efforts to improve the
people's ideological and political awareness as China's reform is
at a crucial stage.
</P>
<P>
Hu made the call during an inspection of east China's Fujian
Province from June 18-24.
</P>
<P>
Hu, who is also a Standing Committee member of the Political
Bureau of Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
visited several counties in west Fujian, an important
revolutionary base for the communists during their fight against
the Nationalists.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president expressed his delight with the tremendous
changes that have taken place in the area, and urged local people
to work for a better economy and a better life.
</P>
<P>
When visiting the site of the Gutian Conference, an important
meeting in the history of the CPC, held 70 years ago, he said that
the meeting emphasized on the importance of enhanced efforts to
improve people's ideological and political awareness, which should
remain a guiding principle today.
</P>
<P>
Hu called on local people to concentrate on economic
development, and urged officials to improve the methods of
ideological and political education to make it more profound and
extensive, and more acceptable to the people.
</P>
<P>
When talking about the nationwide "three emphases" campaign (
putting the emphasis on education in theoretical study, political
awareness and good conduct), the vice-president urged local
officials to implement all measures to clean up the CPC.  
</P>
</TEXT>
