<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Ruling Coalition Discusses Preparation for Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A BN component party leader said the meeting was designed to
discuss the allocation of seats among BN parties in the coming
general election and the BN's preparations and strategies for the
election.
</P>
<P>
The current Parliament's term ends on June 7 next year, but
Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad, who is also the BN chairman,
might call for an early poll this year to take advantage of the
economic recovery and the disarray among opposition parties.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir, who chaired the meeting, ordered BN component parties
to activate their election machinery.
</P>
<P>
"The general election could be called at any time," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said he would personally decide on the final list of
the BN candidates for the general election.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the allocation of seats among BN component
parties would be based more or less on the formula used
previously.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said the general election would be held no later than
June next year. The last general election was held on April 24 and
25, 1995.
</P>
<P>
At Thursday's meeting, BN leaders exchanged views on national
issues which could be used for BN's advantage in the general
election such as the improving economy.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said the leaders concurred that the BN would have to
deal with problems relating to rural development, which has always
been the BN's strongpoint.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether the election campaigning period would be
shortened, Mahathir said it would be of normal duration (less than
two weeks).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
