<HEADLINE> New Securities Fund Introduced in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The three-billion-share Yulong
Securities Investment Fund was put on the market at the Shenzhen
stock exchange today, and a total of 64.9 billion yuan was traded.
</P>
<P>
The closing price was 1.07 yuan a share, up 5.94 percent from
the issue price of 1.01 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The fund purchased close to 1.95 bill yuan-worth of stocks in
five transaction days, which accounts for over 60 percent of its
net assets.
</P>
<P>
It shows the confidence of institutional investors in the
market, said analysts here, who added that they have played a key
role in the recent stock market rally.
</P>
<P>
As the market expands, China's securities watchdog is
greenlighting the introduction of larger funds. Earlier funds had
several hundred million shares, and first two-billion-share fund
was put on the market last year. Yulong is the first three-billion-
share fund this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
