<HEADLINE> Top Trade Union Official Urges Deepening of Anti-corruption Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official has
urged local discipline inspection personnel to deepen the anti-
corruption campaign by taking advantage of the on-going "three
emphases" movement.
</P>
<P>
The nationwide movement, targeting communist party officials at
all levels, puts the emphasis on education in theoretical study,
political awareness and good conduct.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing, member of the Political Bureau of the Standing
Committee of the CPC Central Committee and the secretary of the
CPC Central Commission on Discipline Inspection, said discipline
inspection officials should improve their own political awareness
to better perform their duties.
</P>
<P>
Wei made the remarks during an inspection tour of northwest
China's Gansu Province June 16-24, where he visited enterprises
and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that the present results of anti-corruption
work are far from meeting the requirements of the CPC Central
Committee and the great expectations of the public, even though
some achievements have been made.
</P>
<P>
Party committees and governments at al levels should strengthen
financial management work to prevent the occurrence of corruption
cases, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Anti-corruption work inside enterprises should be combined with
improving enterprise management, he said.
</P>
<P>
Wei, also the chairman of the All-China Federation of Trade
Unions, emphasized the role of trade unions in protecting the
rights and interests of workers, pushing forward reforms in
enterprises, caring for laid-off workers and supervising the
management of enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
