<HEADLINE> Pakistan Capital to Prepare for Possible War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The district administration of
the Pakistani capital Thursday held a high-level meeting to
discuss various steps to deal with any emergency situation in case
of war, an official statement said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, presided over by Deputy Commissioner of Islamabad
Raja Sultan Sikandar, established a "War Book" and reviewed
proposals to activate civil defense, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The deputy commissioner told the meeting that an emergency
control room is being set up to coordinate with all local
institutions and to extend assistance to the citizens.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the local government, power and water
sector, health sector, civil defense, business and commerce and
local police officials attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Official sources have confirmed that anti-aircraft guns have
been installed on the top of some important constructions here,
including the Parliament House, Foreign Office, Pakistan Radio,
Pakistan Television, etc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
