</P>
<P>
-- A mid-level intelligence officer assigned to the CIA
persistently questioned the targeting of a building that turned
out to be the Chinese Embassy in Yugoslavia, but his concerns went
unheeded inside the spy agency and at the U.S. military's European
Command, a senior U.S. intelligence official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
-- President Kim Dae Jung Wednesday defended his policy of
engaging North Korea despite a string of confrontations since last
