Wednesday on the ability of Congress to make Federal law binding
on the states.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- American Airlines is under examination by federal safety
officials for a series of accidents over the past six years,
including the recent one in Arkansas, that all seem to involve
pilot miscues. The inquiry focuses on procedures and training, but
also the culture at the No.2 carrier.
</P>
<P>
-- Immigrant influence in Silicon Valley is growing, according
to a Berkeley study that found ethnic Chinese and Indians run
nearly 25 percent of high-tech firms started there since 1980. The
2,775 immigrant-run companies had sales of 16.8 billion dollars
and employed more than 58,000 in 1998. 
