<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket fell
more than one percent Thursday with interest-rate sensitive
banking stocks taking most of the battering.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index offloaded 30.3 points, or
1.01 percent to 2960.3 points, closing at its low for the day.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index tumbled 56.3 points to 5201.0 and the
all resources index sagged 8.2 to 1173.4 points.
</P>
<P>
The bank index shed 80.7 points to 6547.0, with the nation's
biggest four banks all taking a hit.
</P>
<P>
National Australia Bank offloaded 39 cents to 25.45 Australian
dollars, Westpac bank shed 15.4 cents to 9.796 Australian dollars,
Commonwealth Bank of Australia lost 20.7 cents to 24.40 Australian
dollars and ANZ bank retreated 11.4 cents to 11.206 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the resource sector, diversified resources giant BHP eased
0.7 cent to 16.793 Australian dollars ahead of the release of its
full-year results Friday.
</P>
<P>
Global miner Rio Tinto tumbled 45.3 cents to 23.60 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Gold stocks were buoyed by firmer gold prices, with the
industry sub index climbing 22.2 points to 793.1.
</P>
<P>
The spot price of gold bullion in Sydney closed at 260.65 U.S.
dollars an ounce, 2.00 U.S. dollars up from Wednesday's close of
258.65 U.S. dollars an ounce.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 496.92 million stocks traded for 999.4
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Falling stocks outnumbered rising stocks by 802 to 532 and 535
stocks remained steady. 
</P>
</TEXT>
