<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Singer Mourns Late Chinese Reporters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Bajagic Momcilo-Bajaga, a leading
Yugoslav singer sang songs here today in memory of the three
Chinese reporters killed in the U.S.-led NATO attack on the
Chinese embassy in Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the singing performance in the Yugoslav embassy in
Beijing, Yugoslav Ambassador to China Slobodan Unkovic said that
the Yugoslav people will never forget the support the Chinese
government and people gave them during the NATO air strikes
against their country, and will never forget the three late
Chinese reporters Shao Yunhuan, Xu Xinghu and Zhu Ying.
</P>
<P>
Unkovic expressed his condolences on the late Chinese
reporters, and expressed his gratitude to all Chinese reporters
for telling the world about the truth of the U.S.-led NATO air
strikes.
</P>
<P>
Bajaga sang six songs including the song "My Friends" for an
audience of more than 200.  
</P>
</TEXT>
