<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKMC Sign Reinsurance Agreement with an American Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Mortgage
Corporation Limited (HKMC) signed the Master Mortgage Reinsurance
Policy with the American International Assurance Company Limited
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
HKMC is an affiliate of United Guaranty Mortgage Indemnity
Company.
</P>
<P>
Together with PMI Mortgage Insurance Co., Hang Seng Insurance
Company Limited and Asia Insurance Company Limited, the HKMC has
appointed four Approved Reinsurers to provide reinsurance for the
Mortgage Insurance Program.
</P>
<P>
Under the Program, the HKMC provides mortgage insurance to the
Approved Sellers for an amount up to 15 percent of the value of
the property to enable homebuyers to secure mortgage loans of up
to 85 percent LTV ratio. The HKMC hedges the exposure of the
mortgage insurance by taking out reinsurance with the Approved
Reinsurers.
</P>
<P>
The Mortgage Insurance Program continues to be well received by
the homebuyers. As of June 23, 1999, 740 applications have been
received from 22 Approved Sellers, involving a total mortgage
amount of 1,567 million HK dollars (or 200 million U.S. dollars)
and a total insured amount of 293 million HK dollars (or 37.56
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Secondary property accounts for over 90 percent of the
applications received so far, which indicates that the Program has
served to improve the liquidity of the secondary property market.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
