<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Stresses Senior Citizens' Cultural Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- With the emergence of a bigger
ageing population, the issue of senior citizens' cultural life
should be put on top of the agenda, said Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the number of Chinese aged over 60 has reached 120
million, making up an important part of our society. Therefore,
how to improve their cultural life is essential to social
development and stability, said Li, adding that government
departments at all levels should prioritize this task and improve
the situation by various measures.
</P>
<P>
Carrying out cultural activities is not only the government's
business, but a cause needing the whole of society's involvement.
Cultural and sports facilities should offer convenience and
privileges to senior citizens, and more community services should
be established to help them, Li added.
</P>
<P>
Li also pointed out that cultural and educational departments
should produce more excellent works for senior citizens,
especially those which reflect their lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
