<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 11th Panchen Lama Baptizes Lamas in Xigaze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIGAZE, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The 11th Panchen Lama, one of the
two top religious leaders in Tibet, today baptized lamas and
Buddhists in the Buddhism tradition at the Zhaxi Lhunbo Lamasery,
his main residence, in this second-largest city in southwest China
's Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
It was the first that the nine-year-old Panchen had baptized
lamas and religious followers.
</P>
<P>
The Panchen Lama told the lamas and believers to follow the
instructions of President Jiang Zemin, to love the country and the
religion, safeguard the country and serve the people, and make
contributions to the region's prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
Baptism is a ritual followed by monks of the Tantric sect of
Tibetan Buddhism when they enter a new stage of religious
cultivation.
</P>
<P>
The Panchen Lama entered a tent at 8 o'clock this morning.
Because of its esoteric nature, the ritual was shielded from the
public. One lama explained that the Panchen Lama and two other
Tantric masters had prayed together to instill their power into
the food and water to be distributed among the lamas and followers
to be baptised.
</P>
<P>
The Panchen Lama started to recite the sutra for longevity at
9:20. For the next two hours, he paused now and then to expound
some points when reciting the sutra of 10,000-odd words.
</P>
<P>
"Intelligent and diligent, the Panchen Lama is able to recite
sutras of more than 60,000 words," said Purbu Songzhub, one of the
young Panchen Lama's teachers.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Panchen Lama has an unusual understanding of
the sutras besides his outstanding memory, convincing his
followers that he is the true reincarnation of the last Panchen
Lama, who died in 1989.
</P>
<P>
After the recitation, the Panchen Lama told all present: "All
the lamas of Zhaxi Lhunbo Lamasery, including myself, and the
believers should love the Communist Party of China, love our
socialist motherland and love the religion we believe in."
</P>
<P>
He urged everyone to follow the example of the 10th Panchen
Lama and work for national unity, world peace, and the prosperity
and progress of Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The lamas and believers then were baptized by the 11th Panchen
Lama.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
