<HEADLINE> 38 Narcotics Offenders Sentenced in Shantou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Three courts in this city in south
China's Guangdong Province today handed down various prison
sentences and the death penalty to 38 people convicted of drug
smuggling or trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-three were sentenced five years or longer in prison. Ma
Hongguang and two others were sentenced to death and deprived of
political rights for life.
</P>
<P>
The youngest criminal was 18 years old, and 31 were natives of
Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
The most serious cases involve smuggling or trafficking in 286
to 491 g of heroin.  
</P>
</TEXT>
