<HEADLINE> Giant Killer Dokic Wins Again at Wimbledon Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Australian teenager Jelena Dokic,
who upset world number one and top seed Martina Hingis in the
first round, edged Katarina Studenikova 6-0, 4-6, 8-6 in the
second round here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dokic, 16, had to rally from a 4-2 deficit in the final set to
survive a much closer match against Studenikova, a Slovakian
ranked 114th.
</P>
<P>
Hingis remained the only seeded woman eliminated. No. 9 Mary
Pierce of France reached the third round by beating Italian Rita
Grande 6-1, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
No. 5 Richard Krajicek of the Netherlands, the 1996 champion,
swept past Todd Woodbridge of Australia 7-5, 6-4, 6-4 in a men's
singles second round.
</P>
<P>
Jim Courier advanced beyond the second round at Wimbledon for
the first time since 1993, when he lost in the final to fellow
American Pete Sampras. Courier outlasted 12th-seeded Carlos Moya
of Spain 6-3, 3-6, 7-6 (7-1), 3-6, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Another Spaniard Felix Mantilla, seeded 16th, was later
eliminated by American Paul Goldstein, 6-2, 6-4, 6-7 (5-7), 6-2.
</P>
</TEXT>
