<HEADLINE> Sichuan Intensifies Drug Crackdown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Province in southwest
China has confiscated more than 200 kg of heroin since June last
year, the provincial anti-drug committee announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The province handled nearly 30,000 cases involving drug
trafficking, and also confiscated more than three tons of chemical
products that can be used to make drugs in the one-year period. A
number of drug traffickers were sentenced to death, the committee
said.
</P>
<P>
The progress in the work was partly attributed to the issuing
of a series of strict rules, including the Sichuan Provincial
Regulation on the Banning of Narcotics.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, a total of 74 drug rehabilitation centers have been
set up. Special courses on the dangers of drug abuse have opened
in many high and primary schools in the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
