<HEADLINE> Doohan Might Return in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Mick Doohan, world 500cc motor
cycling champion for the past five years, said on Thursday he
might come back from an injury at the Czech Grand Prix in August.
</P>
<P>
Doohan told a news conference that he would not race again
until he had fully recovered from the injuries he sustained when
he broke his left leg, right collarbone and left wrist in a crash
in qualifying for the Spanish Grand Prix in May.
</P>
<P>
The Australian said that he might make his return at the Czech
Grand Prix in Brno August 22. "It could be a bit sooner or later,"
he said. 
</P>
