<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Death Penalty for Six Drug Traffickers in Urumqi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Six drug traffickers were handed
the death sentence today by Urumqi Intermediate People's Court, in
the capital city of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, northwest
China.
</P>
<P>
The six culprits were caught when trading from 51 to 717 grams
of heroin in 1995 and 1998, in addition to 260 grams of opium.
</P>
<P>
China's Supreme People's Court has verified and approved the
punishment.
</P>
<P>
According to a local source, Xinjiang has handled 154 drug
trafficking cases in the first five months of this year and
punished 91 people, showing China's strong determination to crack
down on drug related crimes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
