<HEADLINE> NPC Members Suggest Vote on Donation Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Participants in the ongoing 10th
meeting of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) Standing
Committee today suggested draft legislation covering donations to
public welfare undertakings be submitted for a vote.
</P>
<P>
They noted that the draft, which has been revised by the
standing committee, has matured and should be submitted to the
session for vote.
</P>
<P>
Many members of the NPC Standing Committee said it is necessary
to adopt a law on donations in order to encourage and regulate
donation activities and protect the interests of both donors and
beneficiaries.
</P>
<P>
Cao Zhi, vice chairman of the committee, said the revised
legislation fully considers suggestions made during the committee'
s previous meeting and should be approved as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Committee member Teng Teng said the most important part of the
revision was the separation of voluntary donations and
solicitations for donations.
</P>
<P>
Some members stressed the draft should provide more specific
incentives in order to encourage businesses to donate to public
welfare undertakings.
</P>
<P>
The draft, which consists 31 articles in six chapters, deals
with issues such as the making and accepting donations, as well as
the use and management of donated assets and related incentives.
</P>
</TEXT>
