<HEADLINE> Russian Farmers Face Prolonged Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There has been almost no rainfall in June in European Russia.
The weather in July will be as hot and arid as in June, said
Russia's Itar-Tass news agency on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Drought has already inflicted damage on 80 percent of the
Rostov region and the Republic of Kalmykia, 40 percent of Saratov,
Volgograd and Orenburg regions, the Republic of Daghestan, and 30
percent of the Voronezh and Belgorod regions, and the Republic of
Bashkiria, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
Russia harvested 47 million tons of grain in 1998, the lowest
in over four decades. This year's output is estimated at 50
million tons, if the harvesting is quick and properly organized,
said experts with the Russian Food and Agriculture Ministry.
</P>
</TEXT>
