<HEADLINE> Heavy Rains Cause Casualties, Material Damage in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Torrential rainfalls in Romania
over the past few days have brought about casualties and material
damages worth 2 billion lei (about 125,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Rivers rose sharply due to the heavy rain, inundating 465
homesteads, 8,500 hectares of farmland and 245 kilometers of roads
and sweeping away 172 bridges.
</P>
<P>
Telephone lines were also cut off in many places and lots of
villages were blacked out.
</P>
<P>
Soldiers and firefighters moved in quickly, but many people are
still stranded in areas difficult to reach.
</P>
<P>
As many as 81 villages and towns in 18 counties of the country
were affected.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasts said rainfalls will continue in the next few
days. 
</P>
