<HEADLINE> 17 Tamil Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
killed 17 Tamil rebels Wednesday in separate clashes in Northern
province, the Defense Ministry announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Government troops killed four rebels and recovered a few
military items in a confrontation with a group of Tamil rebels in
the general area of Kawadikiroykulam Wednesday, military spokesman
Jda Gunasekar said.
</P>
<P>
He said the troops killed four terrorists and wounded two
others in an attack on a terrorist bunker with small arms and
machine guns in the general area of Paranthan the same day.
</P>
<P>
The troops during a fighting patrol observed a group of
terrorists moving into a hut and attacked them with small arms and
machine guns west of Paranthan Wednesday morning, killing four
rebels, he said.
</P>
<P>
Government troops also launched a limited operation in
Thenmaratch to flush out Tamil rebel infiltrators in the early
hours of Wednesday, said the spokesman, adding that five Tamil
rebels were killed in the operation.
</P>
<P>
Tamil rebels have been fighting the Sri Lankan government since
1983 for an independent Tamil homeland in the north and east of
the island nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
