<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Increases College Enrollment Quotas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to new measures introduced
by China's Ministry of Education, an estimated 2.7 million
students will be fortunate enough to enter various institutes of
higher education this year.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Education Ministry said today that China's
ordinary colleges and universities will enroll 1.53 million high
school graduates this year, an increase of 42 percent over 1998.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time that the ministry has increased college
enrollment quotas this year.
</P>
<P>
It set quotas scale at the beginning of this year at 2.3
million, an increase of 230,000 over 1998. It decided to increase
the enrollment quotas by a further 300,000 this time.
</P>
<P>
There is a special quota of 100,000 places allocated for adult
education. The official noted that, if all kinds of higher
education were combined, the total enrollment quota reaches 2.7
million people this year.
</P>
<P>
As most new semesters start in September, it is very urgent for
ministry departments at all levels and colleges to make strenuous
efforts to ensure that the preparation work is completed for
enrollment within guidelines issues by the ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
