<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Session Deliberates Enterprise Legislation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The draft law for solely
individual-funded enterprises should achieve the goal of both
encouraging and regulating the enterprises, according to delegates
to the 10th session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee here today.
</P>
<P>
Members of the NPC Standing Committee said that it is
imperative to have a law dealing with individual-funded
enterprises at a time when the country is developing a socialist
market economy.
</P>
<P>
The draft stipulates that the assets and other legitimate
interests and rights of these enterprises enjoy legal protection.
</P>
<P>
This will define the enterprises' legal status and should have
a positive effect in promoting their further growth.
</P>
<P>
As to whether the solely individual-funded enterprises could
use "company" in their names, the members had different opinions.
</P>
<P>
Some said that this provision is intended to prevent small
businesses from swaggering about and boasting by using big names.
</P>
<P>
Others said that the banning of "company" in the enterprises'
names does not conform with reality and is incompatible with
international practices.
</P>
<P>
In deliberating the draft, some members also voiced their hope
that the legislation contains items related to environmental
protection as some small enterprises are heavy polluters.
</P>
<P>
"Those producing shoddy goods should also be punished," they
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
