<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Ready to Evacuate Residents Near Mayon Volcano </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government assured
the public Thursday it is ready to evacuate residents living near
Mayon volcano in Bicol region in the central Philippines, should
it again show signs of imminent eruption.
</P>
<P>
Secretary Orlando Mercado of the Department of National Defense
said his office has made the necessary arrangements with local
officials in the area.
</P>
<P>
"Our regional officers are ready and organized. We are ready to
evacuate persons," Mercado said in a radio interview Thursday
morning.
</P>
<P>
Mercado also chairs the National Disaster Coordination Council,
which supervises over the Regional Disaster Coordination Council
in Bicol.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Mayon volcano raised fears among local residents
when it emitted ash. Authorities have marked the area within the
volcano's six-kilometer radius as a danger zone.
</P>
<P>
"We don't think the chances of Mayon erupting are that big. The
signs that the volcano is manifesting show that there is less
likelihood of a huge explosion taking place," Mercado said.
</P>
<P>
He added, however, that this does not mean the government has
become complacent. "It would be a tragedy if human lives are
sacrificed because of carelessness," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
