<DOCNO> XIE19990624.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Trounce Ghana 7-0 at Women's World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PORTLAND, June 23 (Xinhua) -- China scored their second straight
victory, trouncing rough-tackle Ghana 7-0 in a Group D match here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, who beat Sweden 2-1 in their first group match
at San Jose, took an early lead through captain Sun Wen who beat the
Ghana team's off-side trap and volleyed past Ghana goal-keeper at
the 9th minute.
</P>
<P>
Sun Wen went on to completed her hat-trick at the 21st and 54th
minutes. She also hit the post twice.
</P>
<P>
The Ghana team, which had one player sent off and other four
booked in their first match against Australia, still adopted a
rough-tackle tactic in the match. They time and again fouled down
Chinese players and earned two yellow cards quickly in the first half.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, with better technique and splendid team-work,
totally out-played their opponents. They were 3-0 up at the 21st
minute with forward Jin Yan also scored one goal at the 18th minute.
</P>
<P>
After taking a 3-0 lead, the Chinese team played relaxed and
seemed satisfied with the scoring as they restrained their
attacking, trying to avoid injury from Ghana's tackle.
</P>
<P>
But the Ghana team would not give up their tactic. In the
second half, they tackled even harder and at the 52nd minute, Regina
Ansah was shown the red card after a brutal foul.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team made two substitutions in the second half, that
allowed young player Zhang Ouying scored twice from bench. Zhao
Lihong also added one in injury time to seal up the 7-0 victory for
China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Ma Yuanan was not overjoyed with the big-margin
win. He said his players played well in the match, but it was not
the time yet to celebrate as the tournament would be tougher and
tougher for China.
</P>
<P>
"I asked my players not to be too excited," Ma said, "We will
have to recover quickly as tomorrow we will have a long journey to
New Jersey."
</P>
<P>
China would be the most travelled team in the tournament. If
they can enter the final, they should travel up to 10,000
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Asked how he could motivated his players for the third match
against Australia since they have already qualified for the
quarter-finals, Ma said:" I would just ask my players to try their
best in every match."
</P>
<P>
Captain Sun Wen, a three-time World Cup player, said after the
match that the victory was no surprise for her.
</P>
<P>
"We knew we could win the match. The great margin is no reason
for us to celebrate as we all know it is not the most important match."
</P>
<P>
Sun said she was not happy with the way the Ghana team
played:"Their tackle tactics was dangerous, some of them were from
the behind. That is a great threat to our team as we could not
afford injuries as we will play the next stage of the tournament."
</P>
<P>
Earlier in a Group C match played here on Wednesday, Russia beat
Japan 5-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
