<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Longest Canal to Be Extended to Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal,
the world's longest, will be extended to the East China Sea as a 1.
8-km-long waterway is dug in the near future in east China's
Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The new waterway will act as a connection linking the existing
Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal and Hangzhou-Ningbo Canal with the
Yongjiang River, which flows into the East China Sea in Ningbo, a
major port city in Zhejiang.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the linking up of the two canals, the river and the
sea will help the Grand Canal to resume its status as a major
transport waterway.
</P>
<P>
The 1,789-km-long Grand Canal runs from Beijing, China's
capital, to Hangzhou, provincial capital of Zhejiang. The digging
of the canal originally started under the order of an emperor of
the Sui Dynasty (581-618).
</P>
<P>
It had been an important transport artery connecting southern
China with northern China, until recently when other means of
transportation became popular.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, a series of projects have been launched to widen
and dredge the southern part of the Grand Canal in a massive
effort to improve its navigational conditions.
</P>
<P>
The latest project is to build five ship locks along the canal
before the year 2002. It will cost more than one billion yuan,
including 53 million U.S. dollars in World Bank loans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990624.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Tea Firm to Float Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The fledgling Dar es Salaam
Stock Exchange (DSE) will soon float shares of the Tanzania Tea
Packers Limited (TaTEPA), the company has said.
</P>
<P>
Press reports Thursday quoted a TaTEPA statement as saying that
25 percent of the company's shares will be floated.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued here Wednesday, did not give the number
of shares to be issued or their price, neither did it tell the
date for the shares floating.
</P>
<P>
"More details of the planned public share offer will be
announced in due course, as the various statutory procedures for
stock exchange listing are followed by the professional team of
bankers, brokers, auditors, lawyers and promoters," the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, TaTEPA Managing Director George Theobald revealed that
an initial public offering may take place in the middle of next
month.
</P>
<P>
Theobald said the Tanzania Venture Capital Fund will be
off-loading a five-percent stake in TaTEPA while the remaining 20
percent offered to the public would be in new shares.
</P>
<P>
At present, only two companies have floated shares at DSE, the
sole stock exchange in Tanzania established in April of 1998.
They are the Tanzania Oxygen Limited and Tanzania Breweries
Limited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
