<DOCNO> XIE19990624.0204 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Opens Legislative Sessions to General Public </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital announced
today the members of the general public will be permitted to
attend sessions of the Municipal People's Congress Standing
Committee, the city's highest legislative body.
</P>
<P>
The regulation, as outlined in the committee's rules of
procedure, was approved during today's 11th session of the 11th
Municipal People's Congress Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
"The decision will increase the transparency of committee
sessions and improve the general public's ability to supervise
lawmakers," according to Wei Yongde, director of the committee's
policy study office.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese capital followed the lead of a number of provinces
and cities which previously introduced regulations allowing the
general public to attend local legislative sessions.
</P>
<P>
The People's Congress is China's basic political system. People
's Congresses at both the national and local levels have been the
pivotal force responsible for supervising and evaluating officials.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Municipal People's Congress is responsible for
drafting laws and regulations covering development and emergency
situations in the city, as well as for appointing and removing
leading officials, including the mayor.
</P>
<P>
Since the 1980s, the Communist Party of China (CPC) has
redoubled efforts to improve transparency in political affairs and
encourage Chinese citizens to study and discuss important state
issues. Related efforts have in turn helped build a clean, honest
and efficient government.
</P>
<P>
"The new decision represents a significant step in promoting
socialist democracy and enhancing the status and influence of the
Chinese capital," according to Wei.
</P>
<P>
The General Office of the Standing Committee is currently
deliberating specific regulations concerning the number of people
allowed to attend sessions, rules of behavior and various other
relevant issues.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
