<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi's Markets Improving Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- There have been considerable
improvements in the rural markets in the south China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region, which has a population of 46 million,
since the reform and opening policy was introduced in the late
1970s.
</P>
<P>
The business turnover of Guangxi's rural markets climbed to 52.
9 billion yuan in 1998 in contrast to a mere 500 million yuan 15
years ago.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi had 3,221 rural markets at the end of 1998, and retail
sales of consumer goods reached 73.4 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Now the business turnover of rural markets accounts for 70
percent of the region's total retail sales volume.
</P>
<P>
And Guangxi's financial markets are also developing steadily.
So far, the region has 36 stock exchange companies and the number
of investors stands at 500,000.
</P>
<P>
The region's stock turnover stood at 74.9 billion yuan last
year. Guangxi now has 42 listed companies which have combined
funds totaling 1.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The region's technology market has also experienced the same
sort of rapid expansion. Since 1995, contracts worth one billion
yuan have been signed for 4,000 technological projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
