<HEADLINE> Chinese University Develops First Virtual Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- A computer lab at East China's
Zhejiang University has successfully developed a CAVE virtual
environment for the first time.
</P>
<P>
CAVE is the world's most advanced virtual reality equipment and
can play a vital role in computer-related research. The CAVE
environment developed by the university's CAD-CG lab, which is one
of China's key state-level labs, has opened the door for Chinese
scientists to do high-level virtual reality research, says one
university official.
</P>
<P>
The university is located in Hangzhou, capital of Zhejiang
Province, and is one of China's most prestigious polytechnic
universities. 
</P>
