<HEADLINE> Wuhan to Become Auto Manufacturing Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Wuhan, capital of Hubei Province in
central China, is currently home to 106 automotive enterprises
with a combined fixed assets of over 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion
U.S. dollars) and is expected to become a new automobile
manufacturing center in the next 3-5 years.
</P>
<P>
By that time, the annual industrial output value for the city's
automobile manufacturing sector is expected to hit 30 billion yuan
(3.6 billion dollars), with taxes rising to five billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The sector now employs over 60,000 people and generates an
industrial output value of some 6.5 billion yuan a year.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government has introduced a series of
preferential policies to accelerate infrastructure construction
and promote the overall development of the industry.
</P>
<P>
A new economic and technological development zone approved by
the central government will provide high quality services for the
Dongfeng-Citroen Automobile Co. Limited. The joint venture, formed
by China Dongfeng Automobile Company and French-based Citroen in
1992, has become a leading car producer in China.
</P>
<P>
The zone has spent over 2.2 billion yuan to construct
infrastructure facilities and has introduced preferential policies
to attract technical personnel.  
</P>
</TEXT>
