<HEADLINE> Velayati to Run for OIC Chief, Daily Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Former Iranian Foreign Minister
Ali Akbar Velayati may run for the future secretary general of
the Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC), local daily
Iran News reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Iran intends to take over the post of OIC secretary general as
the official tenure of the current OIC secretary general Ezzddin
Larak will end this year, the daily said.
</P>
<P>
It is rumored that Iran intended to introduce its candidate
for the post during the recent founding conference of the
Parliamentary Union of the OIC Members end on June 17.
</P>
<P>
In view of the fact that a large number of the OIC members are
Arab states, Iran News said, analysts are reluctant to make
prediction with any degree of certainty on Velayati's nomination.
</P>
<P>
However, the daily said, considering Iran's achievements during
its chairmanship of the OIC, the likelihood of an Iranian being
appointed OIC secretary general is not far-fetched.
</P>
<P>
Velayati served as Iranian foreign minister for 16 years, and
then was appointed advisor on international affairs to the Iranian
supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei in 1997. 
