<HEADLINE> Ningxia Increasing Investment in Highways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region
in northwest China is to invest 1.78 billion yuan in highway
construction this year, a some that equals the combined investment
in this sector for the 1986-95 period, a regional government
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
"Highway construction has enhanced economic links between this
ethnic-concentrated area with neighboring provinces and developed
areas in the country's eastern coast," said Wang Quanshi, vice-
chairman of the regional people's government.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia is one of the smallest inland regions in China with an
area of 66,000 square kilometers and a population of 5.2 million.
With the help of the central government, the mileage of highway
opened to traffic in Ningxia increased by 250 km in each of the
past 17 years.
</P>
<P>
A highway network has been built centered around Yinchuan, the
regional capital, with the total length reaching 9,000 km,
doubling the figure of a decade ago. "Almost all counties have
access to the 13 national or regional highway roads," Wang said.
</P>
