<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Province Sees Tourism Boom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- In spite of the lingering
effects of the Asian financial crisis, China's Guangdong Province
still had a record number of tourists in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists increased 20 percent in the first
quarter year-on-year, with that of foreign tourists up 17 percent.
</P>
<P>
The province's tourism industry has led all of China's
provinces and regions in the number of tourists and tourist
earnings for the past several years.
</P>
<P>
Lu Weixiong, director of the provincial tourist bureau, says
that the province is committed to making strategic corrections
that put an emphasis on services for Chinese and overseas tourists
alike. It also encourages its people to make short tours to see
the beauty of their own province.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the number of Guangdong people visiting their own
province has for the first time surpassed that of those who had
tours outside the province.
</P>
<P>
The province had 51.5 million tourists last year with earnings
from the business exceeding 87.3 billion yuan, including 2.9
billion U.S. dollars worth of foreign exchange. 
</P>
