<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, June 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The Inter-American Development Bank (IDB) on
Wednesday approved 300 million U.S. dollars in financing to
support the 1998-2001 investment program of Aguas Argentina S.A.,
the sole provider of potable water and sewerage services for the
city of Buenos Aires and 13 surrounding municipalities.
</P>
<P>
As of December 1998, Aguas Argentinas supplied potable water
and sewerage service to approximately 7.5 million people and
provided sewerage service to almost six million people. (IDB-
Argentina)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- World foreign direct investment (FDI) inflows in 1998
rose to 644 billion U.S. dollars, 39 percent more than those in
1997, according to the United Nations Conference on Trade and
Development (UNCTAD).
</P>
<P>
"The increase was due largely to a substantial increase in
cross-border mega-mergers and acquisitions (M&AMP;A) among developed
country firms," said the UNCTAD in a press release here Tuesday.
(UN-FDI-Mergers)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- The Dow Jones industrial average fell for a third
straight session Wednesday as investors worried about the Federal
Reserve's next move on interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed down 54.77 at 10,666.86. The index lost 133.93
points in the two previous sessions.
</P>
<P>
Persistent rise in the bond yields made investors uncertain
whether the Federal Reserve will raise interest rates more than
once. The yield on the 30-year Treasury bond rose to 6.11 percent
today from 6.06 percent Tuesday. (US-Wall Street-Closing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- European stock markets fell sharply Wednesday amid
rekindled fears of a hike in US interest rates later this month.
</P>
<P>
The leading UK FTSE 100 finished weaker on fears of interest
rates hikes in the United States. Merger news in Britain failed to
boost sentiment. (EU-Market)
</P>
<P>
