</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesia will continue to see a declining economy
in 1999, but will start to register positive growth in 2000, an
economist said.
</P>
<P>
According to the Pacific Economic Cooperation Council (PECC),
quoted by The Indonesian Observer on Thursday, the Indonesian
economy will grow by 3.7 percent in year 2000 and reach a steady-
state, long-term growth of less than 5 percent beginning 2001. (
Indonesia-Economy)
</P>
