<HEADLINE> Ancient Human Sacrifice Site Found in Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, June 24 (Xinhua) -- A large human sacrifice site dating
back about 3,000 years to the Bronze Age has been found at
Dashanqian village, in Kalaqin Banner in north China's Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Archeologists unearthed more than 60 skeletons of both males
and females, old and young in a pit. Some had been wounded, and
others had been dismembered.
</P>
<P>
The victims were probably captives resulting from an inter-
tribal war or slaves, archeologists said.
</P>
<P>
Also found there were a large amount of grain, pottery
fragments and small bronze objects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
