<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Sacrificial Vessels Unearthed in Ningxia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-eight sacrificial vessels
dating back to the Western Xia kingdom (1038-1227) have been
unearthed in Huinong County, in northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
This is the first batch of Western Xia sacrificial vessels ever
found, said Zhou Xinghua, deputy director of the region's cultural
relics bureau, adding that the vessels are of great significance
for research into metal manufacturing, art technology and
religious affairs of the period.
</P>
<P>
All the vessels are made of bronze. Also unearthed were two
coins.
</P>
<P>
Western Xia was a feudal kingdom whose territory covered the
major part of present-day Ningxia, Gansu, Shaanxi, Qinghai and
Inner Mongolia. When Mongolian troops conquered Western Xia, they
destroyed it almost entirely, leaving very few relics or written
materials relating to it.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990624.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Economy to Grow in 2000: Economist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia will continue to see a
declining economy in 1999, but will start to register positive
growth in 2000, an economist said.
</P>
<P>
According to the Pacific Economic Cooperation Council (PECC),
quoted by The Indonesian Observer on Thursday, the Indonesian
economy will grow by 3.7 percent in year 2000 and reach a
steady-state, long-term growth of less than 5 percent beginning
2001.
</P>
<P>
Suhadi Mangkusuwondo, a senior economist at the Center for
Strategic and International Studies (CSIS), said the PECC economic
outlook is neutral to the outcome of the June 7 election result.
</P>
<P>
The forecast is unlikely to be affected by any change of power
in the government because the new economic paradigm labeled
"people's economy" cannot deviate much from the trend of
market-friendly policies.
</P>
<P>
He said inflation in 1999 will stand at 20 percent but is
showing a continuous downtrend until 2000. The inflation rate is
forecast to reach 15 percent in 2001. Trade financing should
improve gradually with the introduction of a new Export Financing
Agency which will provide subsidized working capital and export
credits for exporters.
</P>
<P>
Slower increases in imports will improve the trade balance but
the surplus will shrink as the growth of imports accelerates in
2000. In 2000 and 2001, other components will contribute
significantly and positively to economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Mangkusuwondo said private investment and bank lending for real
investment are expected to resume and foreign capital will begin
to increase during this period. Government expenditure, however,
will continue to increase but most of the money will be spent on
the social safety net.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the risk in this forecast is largely
political. Should the political assumptions of fresh social chaos
and some sort of power vacuum in the government occur, the economy
could contract by 7 percent in 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
