<HEADLINE> Zhuhai SEZ Economy grows 9.4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Economy in the Zhuhai Special
Economic Zone (SEZ) in south China's Guangdong province grew 9.4
percent in the first five months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Total Gross Domestic Products in the period hit 10.7 billion
yuan, close to the 10-percent growth goal set by the SEZ's
authorities at the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai, a pioneer in China's opening up drive, is one of the
country's five SEZs. The rest are Shenzhen, Shantou, Xiamen, and
Hainan. China established the SEZs and the Pudong New Area in
Shanghai to experiment with bold economic reforms and opening to
the outside world.
</P>
<P>
During the January-May period, the city recorded 447 million
yuan in added agricultural output value thanks to good harvests, a
1.9 percent rise over same period last year.
</P>
<P>
It also had 18.97 billion yuan worth of industrial output value,
up 14.67 percent, and saw remarkable growth in the transport and
telecommunications sectors.
</P>
