<HEADLINE> Chinese Telecoms Equipment Getting Wider Recognition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Satellite telecommunications
equipment with the label "Made in China" is getting greater
recognition here in China's oldest special economic zone.
</P>
<P>
The Runxun Telecommunication Co., one of the major wireless
telecommunications companies in China, has just spent 10 million
yuan on 1,000 satellite receivers developed independently by
Shenzhen's Kingsky Co. Previously, Runxun, like many other pager
companies in China, had imported its telecommunications equipment.
</P>
<P>
"We are very prudent about choosing receiver products," says
Liu Liguang, who is in charge of its technical department, "We
believe that these products can compete technically with imported
devices -- and at half of the price." Savings are important for
domestic pager companies that face increasingly fierce competition,
he explains.
</P>
<P>
Lin Pinglan, Kingsky's general manager, says that China's fast
growing satellite equipment business has caught the interest of
many foreign companies, because it is worth 2 billion yuan
annually and is growing.
</P>
<P>
His company is aiming for a 30 percent share of that market and
expects 30 million yuan in sales this year. That would be triple
last year's sales.
</P>
<P>
The company specializes in satellite data transmission systems
and is a supplier of the Xinhua News Agency and the China
Meteorological Administration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
