<HEADLINE> Colombian Army-Guerrilla Clashes Leave 40 Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Nestor Ramirez, second-in-command of the Colombian Army,
warned at the Ministry of Defense Headquarters that there could be
more deaths to come.
</P>
<P>
The general said that there have been dozens of counterattacks,
performed by soldiers with the aid of helicopters, on three
different fronts against FARC.
</P>
<P>
General Commander of the Military Forces Fernando Tapias
attributed the high number of casualties to surprise attacks made
by FARC guerrillas, the oldest guerrilla group in the country.
</P>
