<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel, Croatia, Slovenia Enter Second Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The 16-team European basketball
championships concluded its preliminary round, with Israel,
Croatia, Germany sailing to the second round on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Slovenia, Lithuania and Italy also booked their second round
berths, together with Yugoslavia and France, as the preliminaries
ended in four French cities.
</P>
<P>
Oded Katash scored Israel's last seven points and hit the
winning jumper to enable his team for the second round with a 64-
62 victory over Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Croatia, upset by Turkey Tuesday, defeated Bosnia-Herzegovina
65-59 behind Toni Kukoc's 11 points, 13 rebounds and seven assists,
Slovenia defeated Hungary 72-66 and Germany beat the Czech
Republic 77-68.
</P>
<P>
Italy beat Turkey 64-61 and Lithuania clinched the last
available place by defeating Greece 82-64.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia kept its perfect record by beating France 63-52, yet
France also qualified after being finished 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Predrag Danilovic's 3-pointer gave Yugoslavia a 44-40 lead with
7:10 left in the game and the two-time defending champion never
looked behind.
</P>
<P>
Slovenia's victory also meant that Spain became the third team
from Group B to advance as Spain later beat Russia 72-69.
</P>
<P>
From Group C, Croatia, Italy and Turkey advanced, all three
teams finished 2-1.
</P>
<P>
In Group D, Lithuania joined Germany and the Czech Republic in
the second round while Greece (0-3) failed to clear the first
round for the first time since it won the title in 1987.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia, France, Israel, Slovenia, Russia and Spain will go
to Pau, while Turkey, Italy, Croatia, Czech Republic, Germany and
Lithuania travel to Le Mans as the second round begins on June 26
and head-to-head results from the preliminary round count.
</P>
</TEXT>
