<DOCNO> XIE19990624.0308 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Resettlement of Dongting Lake Residents Going Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The resettlement of residents
living in areas around Dongting Lake, one of China's largest
freshwater lakes, is going ahead smoothly to pave the way for
building flood-discharging areas there by leveling the embankment
along the lake.
</P>
<P>
As scheduled, the first phase of the relocation project will
make it possible to pull down 161 dykes and embankments which are
located in 23 counties and cities in the province, which will
ultimately add 353 sq. km to the Dongting Lake in Central China's
Hunan province.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May, more than 51,000 families comprising nearly
130,000 people had removed from the lakeside areas, which were
once protected by 153 embankments.
</P>
<P>
Eighty percent of families listed for the first phase of
relocation are expected to be rehoused by the end of June.
</P>
<P>
The local government has issued favorable policies to ensure
the success of the relocation project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
