<HEADLINE> Overseas Specialists to Give Advice on Shenzhen's Urban Planning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- A special committee has been set
up in the economic boom city of Shenzhen in south China's
Guangdong Province to step up the administration of urban planning
and turn the dynamic city into an international metropolis.
</P>
<P>
The urban planning committee has 29 members, with Mayor Li
Zibin as the chairman. It has set up three special sub-committees
under its jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
Twenty six domestic and overseas specialists have been invited
to be advisors to the committee, including seven from Hong Kong
and eight others from Singapore, Japan, Canada, Britain and the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Members of the committee are expected to meet early next month
to discuss the major problems Shenzhen faces in urban construction.
</P>
