<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cholera Epidemic Kills 14 in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAO PAULO, June 23 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of cholera has
killed 14 people in Brazil's northeast state of Pernambuco so far
this year, the highest death toll since 1994.
</P>
<P>
The "Folha de Sao Paulo" newspaper Wednesday quoted sources
from the Health Secretariat of Pernambuco as saying that the
number of deaths from cholera this year almost equaled the total
of 15 victims of the disease in 1997 and 1998 in the same state,
which has been attacked frequently by drought and cholera.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 1,500 cholera cases have been reported so far this year.
</P>
<P>
The worst epidemic of cholera that hit Pernambuco was in 1994,
when 80 people died and 6,942 people were registered as having
been affected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
