<DOCNO> XIE19990624.0312 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Beats Brazil in Women's Volleyball Masters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTREUX, Switzerland, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese women
spikers rallied from the first set down to win three in a row,
beating their Brazilian peers 3-1 here on Wednesday to stand in a
perfect position to win their group in the Swiss Women's
Volleyball Masters Tournament.
</P>
<P>
Through one hour and 36 minutes, the Chinese outpowered the
Brazilians 24-26, 25-23, 25-21 and 25-21.
</P>
<P>
In other games of the day, Russia outscored Canada 25-15, 25-13
and 25-17, while Cuba nipped Italy 25-18, 25-14 and 25-16.
</P>
<P>
As the game will eventually decide the winner of the group,
both China and Brazil fielded in their best strings on the court.
</P>
<P>
In the first set, the Chinese women spikers were clawed back 6-
6 and tied 24-all before they committed errors in receive to
surrender two more points.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the Chinese women were encouraged to keep calm and
to commit less errors, and eventually levelled the score by taking
the see-saw second set.
</P>
<P>
In the third set, the Chinese tied 7-all and 12-all before
setter He Qi scored six straight points in serving.
</P>
<P>
He Qi, together with Zhao Leilei, was ushered in again in the
fourth set after both sides were being tied 11-all, pacing the
Chinese to break ahead for the victory.
</P>
<P>
"This is the toughest match for the reshuffled Chinese women
squad," said head coach Hu Jin, "our players have survived the
mental pressure along the way as both squads overtook each other
time and again."
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, China will take the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
