<HEADLINE> Switzerland Increases Environmental Cooperation With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland's Asea Brown Boveri (
ABB) is stepping up cooperation with China's Tianjin University in
research for cleaner, alternative energy.
</P>
<P>
The project aims to synthesize gasoline from methane and carbon
dioxide.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Baldur Eliasson, who is in charge of the company's energy
and global change department, says that they signed a contract two
months ago and ABB is quite willing to increase cooperation with
China in environmental protection and energy development.
</P>
<P>
In addition to business cooperation, it has also made an effort
at increasing study and research with Chinese partners. It
provided a fund of two million U.S. dollars with the Alliance for
Global Sustainability in May to study the influence of the
electric power system on the environment in China.
</P>
<P>
The energy and environmental protection market in China has
great potential, because at present the per capita energy
consumption in China is only a tenth that of developed countries.
</P>
<P>
ABB is a multinational that deals mainly in electricity,
automation, oil and gas, and fiscal services. It has 16 offices
and 20 enterprises in China, employing over 6,000 people.
</P>
