<HEADLINE> Romanian Runner Fails Doping Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Romanian women runner Cristina
Burca could be banned for life after her positive dope test, said
the Romanian Athletics Federation (FRA) on Wednesday
</P>
<P>
FRA general secretary Nicolae Marasescu said Burca had been
suspended pending a second check, after traces of the steroid
methanolone were found in her sample following the 25-km Berlin
race earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
