<HEADLINE> New- and High-Tech Zones in Hubei Gaining Scale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The fledgling new- and high-
technology development zones in central China's Hubei Province are
regarded as greenhouses of new economic growth to boost the local
industrial economy.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the provincial economic and trade department
reported that Donghu and Wuhan, the two leading technology
development zones in Hubei, realized a total industrial output
value of over seven billion yuan in the January-May period this
year, about 30 percent more than in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Their nearly two billion yuan of increased output value
accounted for 20 percent of the province's total industrial
increased value in the first five months of this year, said a
local economic official.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year, the two technical
development zones helped promote the province's industrial growth
by more than two percentage points to 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
The technical innovation projects which go into production this
year in the province are expected to help promote the province's
industrial growth by five to six percentage points by the end of
this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
The development zones have experienced a prosperous era in
technical innovation investment in recent years, increasing their
total such investment from three billion yuan in 1992 to 24.4
billion yuan last year. The average increase rate has been about
20 percent per year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
