<HEADLINE> Beijing To Process 80 Percent Of Daily Rubbish in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Beijing currently processes more
than 50 percent of its daily rubbish, and anticipates processing
80 percent in the year 2000, according to the Beijing Municipal
Government.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Beijing produced nearly five million tons
of rubbish in 1998, averaging 13,000 tons a day. The city has now
set up eight modern rubbish-processing sites, and the processing
rate has increased from 22 percent in 1995 to the current more
than 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's investment in the construction of environmental
protection infrastructure between 1996 and 2000 will reach 1.1
billion yuan (133 million US dollars), and 100 percent of the
daily rubbish will be processed in 2010, according to the Beijing
Municipal Environmental and Sanitation Management Bureau. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
