<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange on
Wednesday closed with the benchmark IPC index reducing by 136.18
points, or 2.36 percent, at 5,637.35 points from 5,773.52 on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Operators exchanged 79.921 million shares for an amount of 118.
912 million U.S. dollars against 80.982 million shares worth 142.
180 million dollars on the previous day.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.55 to one dollar for
sale and 9.20 for purchase in the main exchange houses of the
Mexico City, compared with 9.50 for sale and 9.20 for purchase on
Monday. 
</P>
