<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Closes 36 Hotels, Restaurants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-six hotels and restaurants
in Shenzhen City in south China have been shut down for failing to
meet safety standards, following a fatal fire which claimed 16
lives and injured eight other people in the city on June 12.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, seven factories and six public entertainment places
in Shajing Town in the city's Bao'an District, where the accident
occurred, were closed five days after the fatal fire.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Shenzhen's fire control department has inspected
over 400 restaurants, hotels, public entertainment places and
factories to check their fire-fighting facilities.
</P>
<P>
The fire ripped through a four-story building in the Zhimao
Electronics Plant, a Taiwanese-funded firm, in Shajing Town on
June 12. The cause of the fire remains unclear, and an
investigation is underway.
</P>
<P>
About 2,380 people were killed and 4,894 injured in a total of
142,000 fires across China in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
