<HEADLINE> Northeast China Police Smash Drug Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Police in Haicheng City in
northeast China's Liaoning Province have smashed a cross-province
drug-trafficking ring and seized 338.4 g of heroin.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off, they arrested two men from Gansu Province
and two others later.
</P>
<P>
The men, aged 22 and 27, respectively, confessed that they had
sold more than 900 g of heroin in Haicheng city.
</P>
<P>
They also gave the police the name of a local drug-seller, who
was also arrested together with two drug addicts.  
</P>
