<DOCNO> XIE19990624.0347 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Warns Possible Violent Reaction to Ocalan Verdict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. State Department on
Wednesday warned American citizens exercise caution while
travelling abroad as an upcoming Turkish court verdict of Abdullah
Ocalan, leader of Kurdistan Workers' party (PKK) might touch off
violent reactions around world.
</P>
<P>
"The court could issue a verdict as early as Friday, June 25,"
the State Department said in a public announcement.
</P>
<P>
"Violent demonstrations took place throughout Europe and in
several other areas worldwide at the time of his capture and could
recur in response to the judicial proceedings," it said.
</P>
<P>
The State Department said U.S. government personnel and
facilities were taking "appropriate security measures."
</P>
<P>
It also urged Americans travelling abroad to exercise caution.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan warned Turkey on Wednesday to beware of a bloodbath that
could unleash a military coup if it executed him.
</P>
<P>
"If capital punishment is inflicted there will be negative
consequences, a lot of blood will flow and the blood could lead to
a military coup d'etat," Ocalan told the Rome Daily La Republica
in an interview conducted through his lawyer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
