<HEADLINE> Lithuanian Lawmaker Asks Israeli Ambassador to Leave </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Vice-chairman Romualdas Ozolas of
the Lithuanian parliament said Wednesday that Israeli Ambassador
Oded Ben Hur must leave the country for doing "everything possible
to set Jews and Lithuanians against each other and slur
Lithuania."
</P>
<P>
Ozolas had proposed sending Ben Hur away in a letter to
Lithuanian Foreign Minister Algirdas Saudargas, the Interfax
reported, quoting sources in Ozolas's secretariat.
</P>
<P>
"It's my conviction that Oded Ben Hur can no longer work as the
Israeli ambassador to Lithuania," the letter said.
</P>
<P>
During a dinner in honor of representatives of the American
Union of Jewish Communities and of the Lithuanian Jewish Community
on Monday, Ben Hur said that "war criminals feel that being in
Lithuania is paradise," Interfax reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
