<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IFC Launches Eurosterling Global Notes Offering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) launched Wednesday a eurosterling 150 million
borrowing (approximately 238 million U.S. dollars) under its
Global Medium Term Note program.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year notes carry a coupon of 5.375 percent and an issue
price of 98.82 percent. The proceeds of the issue were swapped
into U.S. dollar floating rate funds. The issue was lead managed
by Warburg Dillon Read.
</P>
<P>
The funds which IFC raises in the international capital markets
are used to support the operations of IFC, including funding its
lending operations.
</P>
<P>
The mission of IFC, a member of the World Bank Group, is to
promote private sector investment in developing countries, which
will reduce poverty and improve people's lives. IFC's long-term
debt is rated triple-A by both Standard &AMP; Poor's and Moody's
Investors Service. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
